Yorick distributions
--------------------

Here are templates for producing yorick distributions for various open
source software systems.

README.Debian - Instructions for Debian GNU/Linux (and derivatives)

yorick.spec   - RedHat (or Fedora) RPM
                Version, Release must be updated from ../VERSION

yorick        - FreeBSD port, must use
                  md5sum -b yorick-$version.$release.tgz
                to update the yorick/distinfo file (using ./md5 script),
                and update PORTVERSION in yorick/Makefile

yorick.info   - Fink port, must update Source-MD5

md5           - shell script to compute md5 checksum using either
                md5 or md5sum utility
